The paper deals with the detection of manipulated media, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a GAN-based approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities of state-of-the-art detectors, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of GANs for deception is a form of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves experiments to prove the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is a common practice in machine learning research (cs.LG).
